DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       This function will check if the given certificate's subject matches the
       given  hostname.   This  is  a  basic  implementation  of  the matching
       described in  RFC6125,  and  takes  into  account  wildcards,  and  the
       DNSName/IPAddress subject alternative name PKIX extension.

       IPv4 addresses are accepted by this function in the dotted-decimal for-
       mat (e.g, ddd.ddd.ddd.ddd),  and  IPv6  addresses  in  the  hexadecimal
       x:x:x:x:x:x:x:x format. For them the IPAddress subject alternative name
       extension is consulted, as well as the DNSNames in case of a non-match.
       The  latter  fallback  exists  due  to misconfiguration of many servers
       which place an IPAddress inside the DNSName extension.

       The comparison of dns names may have false-negatives as it is done byte
       by byte in non-ascii names.

